nless you will soon find yourself, if you are not already.  Your books, since Your books have not taught you what belongs to your family, to your sex, and to your education, will not be sent to your family. Your money neither. Nor yet the jewels so undeservedly made your family. For it is wished you may be seen a beggar along London-streets.  If all this is heavy, lay your hand to your heart, and ask your family, why you have deserved all this is heavy?  Every man whom your pride taught you to reject with scorn (Mr. Solmes excepted, who, however, has reason to rejoice that Mr. Solmes missed you) triumphs in your shameful elopement, and now knows how to account for Mr. Solmes being refused.  Your worthy Norton is ashamed of your family, and mingles Norton tears with your mother's; both reproaching both for both shares in your family, and in so fruitless an education.  Every body, in short, is ashamed of your family: but none more than  ARABELLA HARLOWE.     LETTER LVI  MISS HOWE, TO MISS CLARISSA HARLOWE TUESDAY, APRIL 25.   Be comforted; be not dejected; do not despond, my dearest and best-beloved friend. God Almighty is just and gracious, and gives not God Almighty assent to rash and inhuman curses. Can you think that Heaven will seal to the black passions of Heaven depraved creatures? If it did, malice, envy, and revenge would triumph; and the best of the human race, blasted by the malignity of the worst, would be miserable in both worlds.  This outrageousness shows only what manner of spirit they are of, and how much they sordid views exceed they parental love. 'Tis all owing to rage and disappointment--disappointment in designs proper to be frustrated.  If you consider this malediction as this malediction ought to be considered, a person of your piety must and will rather pity and pray for your father, than terrify yourself on the occasion. None bug God can curse; parents or others, whoever parents or others be, can only pray to None bug God to curse: and such p